      • getDepth

        public java.lang.Integer getDepth()
        Deprecated.
        Number of degrees of separation (hops) across which lineage should be fetched. A depth of 1 will fetch the immediate upstream and/or downstream assets, while 2 will also fetch the immediate upstream and/or downstream assets of those assets, and so on. A value of 0 will fetch all upstream and/or downstream assets. (BEWARE! This could take a long time and result in a very large response payload.)

      • getDirection

        public AtlanLineageDirection getDirection()
        Deprecated.
        Indicates whether to fetch upstream lineage only, downstream lineage only, or both.

      • getHideProcess

        public java.lang.Boolean getHideProcess()
        Deprecated.
        When true, will only return non-process relations in the lineage. When false, will return the process and non-process relations in lineage. Note: currently processing a graph representation of lineage relies on this being set to true. You will need to parse your own graph from the lineage response if you decide to set this to false.

      • getAllowDeletedProcess

        public java.lang.Boolean getAllowDeletedProcess()
        Deprecated.
        When true, will include deleted processes if hideProcess is set to false. Otherwise, will not return deleted processes.

      • getEntityFilters

        public EntityFilter getEntityFilters()
        Deprecated.
        Filters to apply on entities. Note that if the values in the properties of entityFilters are not valid, then the filter will not be applied and you will receive all values in the response. If your filter seems to be ignored, check that it is valid (if it is invalid it WILL be ignored).

      • getAttributes

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getAttributes()
        Deprecated.
        List of attributes to be returned for each asset.
